\subsection{Torsion order of an elliptic curve}
\begin{definition}\label{ec.torsion_order}
\uses{ec,ec.mordell_weil_group,ec.mordell_weil_theorem,ec.torsion_subgroup}
The **torsion order** of an {{ KNOWL('ec', 'elliptic curve') }} $E$ over a field $K$ is the order of the {{ KNOWL('ec.torsion_subgroup' , title='torsion subgroup')}} $E(K)_{\text{tor}}$ of its {{ KNOWL('ec.mordell_weil_group', 'Mordell-Weil group') }} E(K).  

The torsion subgroup $E(K)_{\text{tor}}$ is the set of all points on $E$ with coordinates in $K$ having finite order in the group $E(K)$.  When $K$ is a number field (for example, when $K=\Q$) it is a finite set, since by the {{ KNOWL('ec.mordell_weil_theorem', 'Mordell-Weil Theorem') }}, $E(K)$ is finitely generated.

When $K=\Q$ the torsion order $n$ satisfies $n\le16$, by a theorem of Mazur.
\end{definition}


